      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model setup procedures must be documented and independently reviewed to mitigate analyst-driven errors.",
      "rationale": "Model setup checklists and boundary condition specifications were documented and cross-checked by a second analyst for each of the three FEA codes, satisfying gradation 2 use error controls."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The chosen model form must be justified relative to the physics governing the quantity of interest.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic continuum FEA with frictional contact at screw-rod interfaces is well-established for ASTM F1717 compression-bending simulation. Material linearity assumption is justified given the sub-yield loading regime. Gradation 3 model form justification is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, geometry, and boundary conditions must be traceable to measured or published sources with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy elastic modulus (114 GPa) and Poisson ratio (0.34) sourced from ASTM F136 material certificates for each physical specimen lot. Geometry derived from CMM measurements of test articles. Uncertainty in material inputs quantified via sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test sample population must be representative and of sufficient size to characterize construct variability.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories provide adequate population for characterizing manufacturing variability. Sample traceability to production lots documented."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span the range of loading scenarios relevant to the validation context.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single compression-bending load configuration per ASTM F1717 protocol. Only one test condition was evaluated, limiting coverage of the loading space. Achieved level 2 is below the required level 3; this deficiency is acknowledged and accepted given the standardized nature of the F1717 protocol."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA input parameters must be demonstrably equivalent to the physical test conditions.",
      "rationale": "CMM-measured specimen geometry was directly imported into each FEA model. Applied loads, displacement boundary conditions, and fixture compliance were matched to laboratory measurements. Input equivalency confirmed by pre-test simulation agreement within 4% on pilot specimens."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics must be defined a priori and applied consistently across all ensemble members.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness (N/mm) and yield load (N) were defined as primary quantities of interest prior to analysis. Ensemble FEA predictions fell within the experimental mean ± 2 standard deviations for both quantities across all N=11 constructs, satisfying gradation 3 output comparison requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
